profile_positions.description:
- Support package design engineering activities in accordance with customer requirements, company`s objectives and policies;
- Support customer RFQ’s, specifications and supplier quotations review related to technical acceptability;
- Participate in bid clarification, pre-inspection, kick-off and other project related meetings;
- Advise management and other Flowserve departments (e.g. CSOA (application engineers), quality, manufacturing, product engineering, test, purchasing) on engineering matters on request;
- Participate in and structure design reviews to control the quality level of the engineering output;
- Maintain and develop the technical expertise level and way of working of the mechanical, electrical, instrument and piping (package design) engineers (and trainees);
- Communicate with suppliers and customers in the technical field;
- Act as a knowledge specialist;
- In depth study of industry codes, standards and customer specifications, conclusions shared and integrated in the way of working for package design engineers;
- Assist in the solution of customer complaints and contribute to the reduction of cost of quality;
- Participate in root cause analysis in order to define corrective and preventive actions;
- Define areas for improvement and standardization;
- Share information, knowledge and experience with other business units within Flowserve.

In this function I was part of a team of engineers who were responsible for the pump/ motor integration assembly, integration into the test set up and test work to verify performance. This included;
- defining and managing of interfaces between several components;
- Design, procurement of base plate to perform pump/ motor assembly; transmission unit (gear
coupling) including torque measurement system and BX-gasket;
- Drafting assembly and hydro test procedures and design reports;
- Design, procurement and manufacturing (test) adaptor and clamp-ring;
- Preparing casting-, machining- and assembly drawings;
- Compensator design, built and (function) test. This included the design and procurement of a separate test skid;
- Performance and mechanical (including multiphase) testing;
- Design (subsea) unit boundary according API 6A/ 17D, ASME VIII div. 1;
- Adjustments to our existing test facility.
